Here's a thorough audit of vyarah.com across SEO, design, content, trust, and features:

🔴 Critical Issues to Fix First
1. Stats show "0+" for Projects & Clients
The counter animation is failing (showing "0+"). This is the first thing visitors see and it kills credibility instantly. Fix the JS counter or hardcode the numbers.
2. Fake social proof notification
The bottom-left popup ("Someone from Mumbai inquired...") is a fabricated trigger. Savvy visitors — especially B2B buyers — recognize this pattern and it damages trust more than it helps. Remove it or use real activity data.
3. No real case studies / proof
The portfolio section has 4 projects but no client names, logos, testimonials, or verifiable results. Anyone can write "3x checkout improvement." Add real client names (with permission), screenshots, or even anonymized logos.

🟠 SEO Improvements
4. Missing meta descriptions & structured data
Your title tag is good, but add a compelling meta description (~155 chars) for each page. Also add:

Organization schema markup
LocalBusiness schema (you're India-based)
FAQ schema for the FAQ section (easy wins in SERPs)

5. No blog / content hub
You sell SEO as a service but have zero content marketing yourself. A blog with articles like "How AI chatbots increased leads by 189% for an e-commerce brand" would drive organic traffic and demonstrate expertise simultaneously.
6. Service pages exist but are likely thin
/services/ai-automation, /services/web-development etc. are linked — make sure each is a full, keyword-rich page, not a stub. These are your money pages.
7. Alt text & image optimization
Ensure all images have descriptive alt text for accessibility and image SEO.

🟡 Trust & Conversion
8. No team page / founder face
AI agency buying decisions are relationship-driven. Who is behind Vyarah? A founder photo + 2-line bio dramatically increases trust, especially for ₹1.5L+ engagements.
9. Testimonials are missing
There are zero client quotes anywhere on the page. This is a major gap for a services business. Even 3 real testimonials (name + company + outcome) would significantly improve conversion.
10. ROI Calculator is good — but disconnected
The calculator is a smart feature, but after showing "Potential Uplift +₹7.5L" there's no immediate, frictionless CTA (like a pre-filled WhatsApp message quoting those numbers). Connect the output to the action.
11. Pricing anchoring
"₹49,999 onwards" is vague. "Onwards" creates uncertainty. Consider replacing with a clearer starting point or a "Get a Quote in 24hrs" promise tied to the contact form.


13. Free audit / lead magnet
You mention "Request Free Audit" in the CTA but there's no landing page for it. Build a short audit form (5 questions about their business) that delivers a PDF report — this captures leads with much higher intent.
14. Case study pages
Turn each portfolio item into its own URL (/work/ecommerce-growth-engine) with the full story: problem → solution → results. These rank well and are powerful sales tools.
15. Newsletter / lead nurture
The footer has a "Stay Updated" section with no input field. Either add the email capture form or remove it — a broken/missing form looks sloppy.

🔵 Minor Polish
